perty is false for handling 404 errors as NonTransient. I think I might end up with two tests. I also want to verify that the RetryTemplate properly counts retries using an atomic integer. I’m trying to understand the difference between \\\"max-attempts\\\" and \\\"maxRetries\\\" in the context of Spring, and what they really imply. I wonder if I should assert that attempts are between 2 and 3 or test with just max-attempts=1 for clarity. I might need to inspect the RetryPolicy semantics further.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5zlSVkqho8Mlu8diSk7dyzoA|fc_0cbf29b1a9ed1f52016a3f391c522c8190a8f7f50b958a59ef", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "J=$(find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.springframework/spring-core/7.0.7 -type f -name '*.jar' | head -1); javap -classpath \"$J\" -c -p org.springframework.core.retry.RetryPolicy | sed -n '1,260p'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1221, "output": 587, "cacheRead": 34304, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36112, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782528273395, "responseId": "resp_0cbf29b1a9ed1f52016a3f39120cd08190b71f532f533edf3f"}}
